The Bundesbank will not hold a newsconference after its regular fortnightly central bank councilmeeting on Thursday, a spokesman said in answer to enquiries.    The council is meeting in West Berlin, where it meets oncea year. It also meets once a year in another German city. Thesemeetings outside Frankfurt are traditionally followed by a newsconference. The spokesman declined to comment further.    In Bonn a finance ministry spokesman said Finance MinisterGerhard Stoltenberg would take part in the meeting in WestBerlin. His participation was arranged long ago, he added. REUTER&#3;